# .npmrc — npm registry configuration for this project
#
# Routes @chamber-19/* packages to GitHub Packages (npm.pkg.github.com).
# The auth token is read from the NODE_AUTH_TOKEN environment variable —
# never hardcoded here so this file is safe to commit.
#
# Local development:
#   1. Create a GitHub classic PAT at https://github.com/settings/tokens/new
#      with the `read:packages` scope.
#   2. Set the env var before running `npm install` in this directory:
#
#      macOS/Linux:
#        export NODE_AUTH_TOKEN=ghp_yourTokenHere
#        npm install
#
#      Windows PowerShell:
#        $env:NODE_AUTH_TOKEN = "ghp_yourTokenHere"
#        npm install
#
#   After install the env var is no longer needed for development —
#   only for re-running `npm install` or `npm ci`.
#
# CI: the CHAMBER19_PACKAGES_TOKEN secret is passed as NODE_AUTH_TOKEN
#     on the `npm ci` step in .github/workflows/release.yml.

@chamber-19:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}
